block pageContent
  main
    section
      +header("About me")

      .grid
        .grid__item
          div
            p.lead I’m Mike Carter, an experienced full-stack developer and technical lead, building on the web since 2006.

            .profile-gallery
              img.profile-gallery__image(src="/assets/images/profile/mike-carter-1.jpeg" alt="Mike Carter climbing a hill in the snow" width="157" height="157" loading="lazy")
              img.profile-gallery__image(src="/assets/images/profile/mike-carter-2.jpeg" alt="Mike Carter standing with his family in front of a waterfall" width="157" height="157" loading="lazy")
              img.profile-gallery__image(src="/assets/images/profile/mike-carter-3.jpeg" alt="Mike Carter wearing a tiara" width="157" height="157" loading="lazy")


            p I’ve worked with teams of all and led many digital transformations through the companies I’ve founded, and I’m at my best collaborating with others to deliver high quality web applications that solve valuable problems.

            p I've been at this for 2 decades now, and find myself just as excited by AI today as I was by publishing handwritten HTML and CSS when I started. If you'd like to work together, just <a href="mailto:mike@mcarter.me">email me</a>.

        .grid__item
          .card
            h3 Skills &amp; Technologies
            ul.technologies
              li <strong>AI</strong> &#9758; <a href="https://claude.com/product/claude-code" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Claude Code</a>, <a href="https://cursor.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Cursor</a>, AI-assisted refactoring & code analysis, prompt engineering and agent orchestration for development workflows.
              li <strong>Backend</strong> &#9758; <a href="https://nodejs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Node.js</a>/<a href="http://typescriptlang.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">TypeScript</a>, <a href="https://www.ruby-lang.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Ruby</a>/<a href="https://rubyonrails.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Ruby on Rails</a>, <a href="https://www.mysql.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">MySQL</a>/<a href="https://www.postgresql.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">PostgreSQL</a>, <a href="https://redis.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Redis</a>, API design.
              li <strong>Frontend</strong> &#9758; <a href="https://react.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">React</a>/<a href="http://typescriptlang.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">TypeScript</a>, <a href="https://nextjs.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Next.js</a>, SPA architecture, state management, high-volume user flows.
              li <strong>Mobile</strong> &#9758; <a href="https://reactnative.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">React Native</a> &amp; <a href="https://native.hotwired.dev/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Hotwire Native</a>, push notifications, authentication, real-time messaging.
              li <strong>Cloud infrastructure</strong> &#9758; AWS (<a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ecr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">ECR</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ecs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">ECS</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">EC2</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/rds/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">RDS</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/lambda/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Lambda</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/cloudfront/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">Cloudfront</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/s3/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">S3</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/ses/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">SES</a>, <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/sns/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="technologies__link">SNS</a>), scalable systems design.
              li <strong>DevOps</strong> &#9758; Continuous Itegration (CI) &amp; Deployment (CD), automated testing, monitoring.

    section#work-history
